Network install configuration
=============================

Type name: netinstall

The name of a netinstall is structured as "<OS>-<Variant>", where
variant may not contain a "-".

Represents a specific variant of configuration choices for network
installation of an operating system.

Palletjack2pxelinux uses "host.os.name" and "host.kickstart.variant"
to generate os variant enumeration PXE menus and os variant
installation PXE menus.

Links:

  netinstall/<os>/os -> ../../os/<name>


Files:

  netinstall/<os>/<variant>/kickstart.yaml


Transformed values:

  host:
    kickstart:
      variant: Variant part of netinstall name